text:
Passengers onboard a Hawaiian Airlines flight from New Zealand to Hawaii got to celebrate the start of 2018 twice.
Hawaii Airlines Flight no. 446 took off from Auckland at 12:05 a.m. on New Year's Day.
It landed in Honolulu at 10:15 a.m. on New Year's Eve.
Twitter account @Flightradar24 noted the flight's progression with this note: "Time travel is possible."
The jump back into 2017 almost didn't happen.
The flight was scheduled to take off at 11:55 p.m. Sunday, but left about 10 minutes late.
Time travel is possible!
Flight #HA446 just took off from New Zealand in 2018 and will land in Hawaii back in 2017! pic.twitter.com/3KsCEniCOL — Flightradar24 (@flightradar24) December 31, 2017
